data.description: New roof in 2020, new HVAC in 2017. Eligible for USDA Rural Housing! Welcome to 344 Bridleridge Road! This beautiful, 3 BR / 2.5 BA home is located in the very popular Bridleridge subdivision in Lexington. Zoned for Lexington One’s award-winning schools, this beautiful home is perfect for the first time home buyer or small, growing family. Like space? This home is situated on a 1.11 acre lot! This home is so charming with its beautiful front porch and pristine landscaping. As you walk in the front door, You’ll notice the modern paint, LVP flooring throughout the lower level, and brand new carpet in the formal living room. The kitchen is spacious with an island and it opens up into the living room, complete with a cozy fireplace. The formal dining room is a nice size and would allow the new owners to host a lovely dinner party or Thanksgiving meal. As you go up the stairs, you will notice the two spacious bedrooms with private closets. The master bedroom is cozy and provides a wonderful sanctuary. There’s lots of counter space on the vanity, a spacious garden tub, a separate shower, and a nice closet. it’s wonderful! Finally, there’s nothing quite like walking out the back door and spending time on your wonderful deck overlooking your spacious backyard. Note, there’s nothing but woods behind you, so this is a very private section of the neighborhood. Your new lot goes past the fence! There’s so much to see here. Schedule a showing today before it’s gone!
